podcast is the perfect source for iOS and Swift developers looking to stay up-to-date on the latest news and trends in the field. With helpful advice from experienced developers, Jaime Lopez, Mark Rubin, and Tim Mitra, , it‚Äôs the perfect way to stay informed and inspired. Join us for the latest mobile development news, notes and tech tips for developers.", imageUrl: "https://mtjc.fm/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/mtjc-keys-wt-1000.png")), .init(id: "a7e90ede-2dea-4f2d-8374-58dcca2ee40e", name: "PODCAST | Radio Host Opens Up About \"Emotional\" Breakup", description: "<p>On today\'s podcast, Adam McGuire is back in the hot seat for Allan alongside Carly and he opens up about a difficult change happening in his life.</p>\n<p>Listeners define what constitutes as being \"late\" to work...</p>\n<p>Plus, The FAME Game is back - Can you tell the difference between a Taylor Swift song and a candle scent?!</p>\n<p>¬†</p><p>See <a href=\"https://omnystudio.com/listener\">omnystudio.com/listener</a> for privacy information.</p>", audioUrl: "https://traffic.omny.fm/d/clips/566281f8-200e-4c9f-8378-a4870055423b/fbafe55f-bce3-435d-a3c5-a8680173d61e/6812c1aa-5989-4ff1-b9af-b1780010583d/audio.mp3?utm_source=Podcast&in_playlist=33e71063-2e88-4c86-a551-a86801741c48", subtitle: "", datePublished: 1716340110, duration: 1606, podcastSeries: PodsLab.PodcastSeries(id: "4b3712c9-98d0-44a2-9cc2-5a1dd6527740", name: "Allan & Carly  Catch Up - Hit WA", description: "<p>Wake up with Allan &amp; Carly across WA!</p>", imageUrl: "https://www.omnycontent.com/d/programs/566281f8-200e-4c9f-8378-a4870055423b/fbafe55f-bce3-435d-a3c5-a8680173d61e/image.jpg?t=1679533064&size=Large")), .init(id: "5eb5f94e-74e1-474b-945b-6ae8858ff4d5", name: "Ep. #9 | Mayank Gupta: Writing a Top 100 Interview Questions Book & Building a Brand!", description: "<p>üöÄ Excited to share the latest episode of Swift and Tips Podcast featuring my friend and iOS developer, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/mayank-gupta-27673a125/\">Mayank Gupta</a>! üéôÔ∏è</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Mayank dives into the fascinating journey of writing an interview book with the top 100 questions and the unique challenges he faced in becoming an entrepreneur. üìöüíº</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>He also reveals how creating content accelerated his path to landing his first iOS job faster than he ever imagined! üé•üë®‚Äçüíª</p>\n<p>This episode is packed with valuable insights for anyone looking to enhance their career or break into entrepreneurship in the tech world. </p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Cracking The iOS Interview: https://www.swiftanytime.com/cracking-the-ios-interview\n\nCracking the Mobile System Design Interview: https://www.swiftanytime.com/cracking-mobile-system-design-interview\n\nMayank&#39;s Social Media: \nhttps://www.swiftanytime.com/\nhttps://twitter.com/swiftanytime\nhttps://twitter.com/iosmayank\nhttps://www.youtube.com/@UCPgfAA83ROUVM-E3NCY154A \n\n-----\n\nMy Contact: \nhttps://www.swiftandtips.com\nhttps://twitter.com/swiftandtips\nhttps://iosdev.space/@swiftandtips\nhttps://www.linkedin.com/in/pedrorojaslo/</p>\n", audioUrl: "https://anchor.fm/s/f40ca194/podcast/play/87025300/https%3A%2F%2Fd3ctxlq1ktw2nl.cloudfront.net%2Fstaging%2F2024-4-21%2F46590048-b8c9-cef4-193d-b0ed95fdbe8b.m4a", subtitle: "", datePublished: 1716299951, duration: 5074, podcastSeries: PodsLab.PodcastSeries(id: "7a6c53ea-a8a7-4d7f-8832-f913ee31c965", name: "Swift and Tips Podcast", description: "This is Swift &amp;&amp; Tips! Discovering how Swift works under the hood ü§ì.", imageUrl: "https://d3t3ozftmdmh3i.cloudfront.net/staging/podcast_uploaded_nologo/40844685/40844685-1711428318588-4968f145abd23.jpg")), .init(id: "e013c128-44dd-4a68-a240-effbdcbb94d5", name: "Listener Question - How do we combat the rising tide of cross platform on mobile?", description: "<p><br>Thanks for the suggestion on this topic. We often see folks asking why cross-platform is such a great idea, but we don\'t usually discuss why it can also be a bad idea and how we can promote native platform development.</p><p><br>This can be incredibly challenging for companies that see the one code base for cross-platform development as reduced development time and cost without considering the long-term consequences.</p><p><br></p><ul><li>(00:00) - Introduction</li>\n<li>(01:10) - DevClub Discord</li>\n<li>(01:27) - Listener Question</li>\n<li>(06:34) - Become a Patreon member</li>\n<li>(06:54) - Native code is easier to maintain</li>\n<li>(10:44) - Rate and review</li>\n<li>(11:42) - Support the podcast</li>\n</ul><br><strong>Become a Patreon member and help this Podcast survive</strong><br><a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/compileswift\">https://www.patreon.com/compileswift</a><p><strong>Please leave a review and show your support</strong><br><a href=\"https://lovethepodcast.com/compileswift\">https://lovethepodcast.com/compileswift</a></p><p><strong>You can also show your support by buying me a coffee</strong><br><a href=\"https://peterwitham.com/bmc\">https://peterwitham.com/bmc</a></p><p><strong>Follow me on Mastodon</strong><br><a href=\"https://iosdev.space/@Compileswift\">https://iosdev.space/@Compileswift</a></p>\n<strong>Thanks to our monthly supporters</strong>\n<ul>\n  <li>Arclite </li>\n</ul>\n<strong>\n  <a href=\"https://patreon.com/compileswift\" rel=\"payment\" title=\"‚òÖ Support this podcast on Patreon ‚òÖ\">‚òÖ Support this podcast on Patreon ‚òÖ</a>\n</strong>", audioUrl: "https://media.transistor.fm/a84109b8/4e974545.mp3", subtitle: "", datePublished: 1716268304, duration: 819, podcastSeries: PodsLab.PodcastSeries(id: "ff229cf8-0ec5-4c14-a708-91359e31285a", name: "Swift Developer Podcast - App development and discussion", description: "Dive into the world of software development for Apple\'s diverse range of devices. Tune in for in-depth interviews with industry experts and the latest information. Whether you\'re an experienced developer or just starting, this podcast is your one-stop shop for everyth